# GitHub Essental Commands

- git init :
initialize and track the current working direcotry

- git status : 
check the status of the git directory (changes to be made/commits etc)

- git add :
add a commit to be changed

- git commit :
commit changes to files in the repo

git commit -a to add and commit at once

- git diff :
show differences for files/branches/tags before/after commits 

- git rm {file} :
remove file

- .gitignore :
Files to be ignored for commiting 
For files to be escaped from this rule, add a ! before the file/path

- git branch :
Branch into a new parallel repository
-d - delete a branch 

- git checkout / git switch :
Cd into this new repository

- git log :
log and summary
git log --graph --all --oneline (concise verison)
git log --oneline --decorate (condensed commit history with tags)

- git merge :
merge one repository with another 

- git tag : {"tagname"}
give names to specific points in the history of our project

- git remote add origin: { https://github.com/user/git_tutorial.git }
Add a remote address to your local repo

- git remote -v :
what remote location is connected to your local Git clone

- git push origin main :
Sync remote and local repository

- git pull :
Downloads commits to local repository and merges them

- git clone : { https://user@github.com/user/git_tutorial.git .}
Clone a repository from remote to local 

- git branch --set-upstream-to origin/main :
Always push commits to origin/main on remote

- git fetch :
download remote changes without merging them

- git push origin --delete trimming :
Delete branch from remote

- git push --tags :
Push tags to remote

#Use relevant verison to reproduce analysis
git clone {repo} followed by git checkout {tag}


